This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as extractive summarization and multi-label classification, which are commonly studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also employs multi-task learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for improving model performance. The use of RNN-based classifiers suggests a focus on sequence modeling, which is also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks.
